# resize partition
1. sudo fdisk /dev/sda. delete sda1,sda2,sda3,sda4, and create a new primary partition sda1 
2. sudo reboot
3. sudo resize2fs /dev/sda1

https://askubuntu.com/questions/66000/how-to-merge-partitions
https://askubuntu.com/questions/329875/root-partition-size-remains-same-after-partition-resize-with-gparted

